1
00:00:01,240 --> 00:00:03,810
(Episode 99)

2
00:00:05,310 --> 00:00:07,150
General Manager Kang,
something awful happened.

3
00:00:08,750 --> 00:00:11,950
Your mother found out everything.

4
00:00:12,420 --> 00:00:13,520
What are you talking about?

5
00:00:14,150 --> 00:00:15,320
What do you mean, "everything?"

6
00:00:15,750 --> 00:00:18,820
That you're CEO Chae's biological son.

7
00:00:19,090 --> 00:00:20,090
What?

8
00:00:20,160 --> 00:00:22,860
I think she stormed the Chairman's home
after she found out.

9
00:00:23,960 --> 00:00:24,960
What are we going to do?

10
00:00:29,400 --> 00:00:31,640
How could you leave your son with me,

11
00:00:31,700 --> 00:00:34,870
then have an affair with my husband
and ruin my family?

12
00:00:34,940 --> 00:00:36,710
Get off me!

13
00:00:37,280 --> 00:00:40,250
You don't deserve to be a mother.

14
00:00:40,410 --> 00:00:43,150
You're not a mother, you're a monster!
A monster, you hear me?

15
00:00:47,590 --> 00:00:48,590
Lawyer Han.

16
00:00:51,390 --> 00:00:55,290
I think there's been a misunderstanding.
Please, calm down.

17
00:00:55,660 --> 00:00:59,960
Just calm down and let's talk outside.
We can clear this all up.

18
00:01:02,700 --> 00:01:03,700
"Misunderstanding?"

19
00:01:04,140 --> 00:01:05,770
Don't give me that nonsense!

20
00:01:06,870 --> 00:01:11,240
I wouldn't forgive you even if you begged!
What misunderstanding?

21
00:01:11,310 --> 00:01:13,710
Han Young Ja,
are you really going to do this?

22
00:01:14,210 --> 00:01:17,280
You can't even keep your husband in line.
Who are you to be yelling?

23
00:01:18,250 --> 00:01:20,250
What in the world is going on here?

24
00:01:22,120 --> 00:01:24,690
Father, it's nothing.

25
00:01:28,930 --> 00:01:29,930
Chairman.

26
00:01:30,300 --> 00:01:33,470
Jun Ho's birth mother is Chae Hwa Young.

27
00:01:34,030 --> 00:01:37,800
Chae Hwa Young is the one
who gave birth to my eldest son, Jun Ho.

28
00:01:38,200 --> 00:01:42,240
- And you think this is nothing?
- What did you say?

29
00:01:42,910 --> 00:01:43,940
Kang Jun Ho is...

30
00:01:44,940 --> 00:01:46,780
Chae Hwa Young's son?

31
00:01:47,680 --> 00:01:51,950
That's not true, Father.
She's mistaken. Yeom San Wol.

32
00:01:52,050 --> 00:01:55,450
Don't just stand there gawking.
Get this woman out of here, now.

33
00:01:56,150 --> 00:01:58,190
Why?
This is just starting to get interesting.

34
00:01:59,520 --> 00:02:03,060
- Get out! Stop spouting nonsense!
- Get out of my way!

35
00:02:03,730 --> 00:02:04,860
Nonsense?

36
00:02:06,560 --> 00:02:11,200
Chairman, Chae Hwa Young is still seeing
my husband.

37
00:02:12,070 --> 00:02:14,910
She's dreaming of the three of them
becoming a family.

38
00:02:15,470 --> 00:02:18,940
- Does this make any sense to you?
- Shut up. Who told you that?

39
00:02:21,250 --> 00:02:22,250
Then,

40
00:02:23,210 --> 00:02:24,750
are you saying Jun Ho isn't your son?

41
00:02:26,180 --> 00:02:30,990
Say it.
Say it right here in front of everyone.

42
00:02:31,460 --> 00:02:34,230
"Kang Jun Ho is not my son."
Go on, say it!

43
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:41,900
- Well...
- He is your son, isn't he?

44
00:02:43,230 --> 00:02:46,100
The son you gave birth to
and abandoned at an orphanage!

45
00:02:46,370 --> 00:02:47,570
And that son is Jun Ho.

46
00:02:47,910 --> 00:02:50,880
And you seduced my husband,
who raised him, didn't you?

47
00:02:51,240 --> 00:02:54,210
And now you're trying
to make him divorce me,

48
00:02:54,780 --> 00:02:57,850
so the three of you can live together
as a family, right?

49
00:02:58,180 --> 00:02:59,180
Am I wrong?

50
00:03:00,750 --> 00:03:04,420
- Stop it! Just stop and get out of here!
- Seo Rin.

51
00:03:05,020 --> 00:03:06,820
Did you know about this too?

52
00:03:06,930 --> 00:03:09,760
I don't care whose son Jun Ho is.

53
00:03:10,300 --> 00:03:12,660
No matter what anyone says,
I'm going to marry him!

54
00:03:14,670 --> 00:03:15,670
You think this is funny?

55
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:17,140
Don't even dream of it.

56
00:03:17,800 --> 00:03:19,170
Jun Ho is my son,

57
00:03:19,870 --> 00:03:22,740
- and I'll never give you Kang Nam Bong.
- Shut up, Han Young Ja.

58
00:03:22,810 --> 00:03:24,380
That's enough, both of you!

59
00:03:25,180 --> 00:03:26,780
- Goodness!
- Oh!

60
00:03:26,840 --> 00:03:27,950
Oh no, Chairman!

61
00:03:34,390 --> 00:03:35,520
Oh, Jang Mi.

62
00:03:36,120 --> 00:03:39,720
- It's absolute chaos here right now.
- What?

63
00:03:40,830 --> 00:03:42,260
Lawyer Han showed up...

64
00:03:42,530 --> 00:03:44,800
and revealed that Jun Ho is
Chae Hwa Young's son?

65
00:03:45,030 --> 00:03:48,030
- Wait, my mom did that?
- Grandfather must be in complete shock.

66
00:03:48,770 --> 00:03:50,100
Okay, I'm on my way.

67
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:54,770
Baek Ho, what are we going
to do about your mother?

68
00:03:55,040 --> 00:03:57,310
So my mom finally found out.

69
00:03:58,540 --> 00:04:00,110
That my brother is CEO Chae's son...

70
00:04:00,510 --> 00:04:03,080
- and Chairman Ma found out too?
- Yes.

71
00:04:03,550 --> 00:04:06,280
How do you think your mother found out?

72
00:04:17,900 --> 00:04:22,170
- Father, please forgive me this once.
- What more could I possibly forgive?

73
00:04:22,270 --> 00:04:25,370
Father, I never meant to deceive you.

74
00:04:25,470 --> 00:04:28,270
What nerve, spouting such lies.

75
00:04:28,510 --> 00:04:30,640
I had forgotten all about the boy myself.

76
00:04:31,480 --> 00:04:33,610
Then, I started looking for him,
just in case...

77
00:04:33,910 --> 00:04:37,880
I thought he had died of leukemia,
but somehow, he was still alive.

78
00:04:39,450 --> 00:04:43,990
I only recently learned he was my son
and began seeing him. Believe me, Father.

79
00:04:44,060 --> 00:04:48,830
So you dared to marry your son
to the daughter you stole,

80
00:04:49,190 --> 00:04:51,160
to try and take over Dream Group?

81
00:04:51,560 --> 00:04:55,200
That's not true, Father.
I would never dream of it.

82
00:04:55,270 --> 00:04:58,340
I've long known you were
more than capable of it.

83
00:04:59,940 --> 00:05:02,370
I've heard enough. Get out.

84
00:05:02,640 --> 00:05:05,080
Father, please, leave Jun Ho out of this.

85
00:05:05,510 --> 00:05:09,110
- Jun Ho is innocent.
- Didn't you hear me? I said get out!

86
00:05:20,220 --> 00:05:21,630
That old bastard, Ma Dae Chang.

87
00:05:21,990 --> 00:05:25,030
So that's it. He's declared war,
daring to come after my son.

88
00:05:27,030 --> 00:05:30,000
Even after I begged and pleaded,
he doesn't even bat an eye?

89
00:05:31,270 --> 00:05:34,670
That monster. What do I do?

90
00:05:35,340 --> 00:05:36,510
What am I supposed to do?

91
00:05:44,880 --> 00:05:46,550
I heard you went to Chairman Ma's house.

92
00:05:47,450 --> 00:05:51,290
- I did.
- Did you have to tell him all that?

93
00:05:51,790 --> 00:05:54,790
About Chae Hwa Young
being your birth mother.

94
00:05:55,390 --> 00:05:56,390
When did you find out?

95
00:05:56,530 --> 00:06:00,230
- Why does it matter when I found out?
- So, knowing all that,

96
00:06:01,670 --> 00:06:03,700
and you knew Kang Nam Bong was meeting
with Chae Hwa Young, didn't you?

97
00:06:04,240 --> 00:06:05,300
And knowing everything,

98
00:06:06,740 --> 00:06:08,110
you were still planning
on getting married?

99
00:06:09,040 --> 00:06:10,440
How could you deceive me like that?

100
00:06:11,010 --> 00:06:12,280
I'm sorry for that, Mother.

101
00:06:13,280 --> 00:06:14,280
Tell me.

102
00:06:14,980 --> 00:06:16,450
Was the pull of blood that strong?

103
00:06:18,520 --> 00:06:19,520
I...

104
00:06:20,690 --> 00:06:22,850
saw you through your battle with leukemia,

105
00:06:23,220 --> 00:06:24,720
and raised you like the most
precious thing on earth.

106
00:06:26,390 --> 00:06:27,390
And yet,

107
00:06:28,760 --> 00:06:30,090
I have never felt so betrayed.

108
00:06:31,960 --> 00:06:33,870
You can't do this to me.

109
00:06:34,430 --> 00:06:35,630
How could you do this to me?

110
00:06:35,770 --> 00:06:38,100
What have I done to make
you treat me like this?

111
00:06:38,170 --> 00:06:41,540
You knew that Chae Hwa Young
was your birth mother,

112
00:06:42,510 --> 00:06:44,040
and you didn't say a single word to me.

113
00:06:44,780 --> 00:06:45,780
If I hadn't found out,

114
00:06:46,040 --> 00:06:49,410
you would have kept me
in the dark forever, right?

115
00:06:49,680 --> 00:06:51,720
All while laughing it up
with your birth mother!

116
00:06:54,790 --> 00:06:55,990
Why aren't you saying anything?

117
00:06:57,490 --> 00:06:58,490
Well?

118
00:06:59,720 --> 00:07:00,930
Tell me I'm wrong!

119
00:07:01,490 --> 00:07:02,560
That for you...

120
00:07:03,630 --> 00:07:06,400
that I'm the only mother you have!

121
00:07:07,400 --> 00:07:10,470
Why so silent?
Why can't you even lie for my sake?

122
00:07:10,540 --> 00:07:12,370
Please, Mother. That's enough.

123
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:15,940
- You know better than anyone, Mother.
- What do I know? What?

124
00:07:16,140 --> 00:07:18,280
I'm so grateful for you, Mother.

125
00:07:18,880 --> 00:07:22,680
I even pushed CEO Chae away,
telling her you're my only mother.

126
00:07:22,850 --> 00:07:23,850
And?

127
00:07:27,420 --> 00:07:28,420
But...

128
00:07:30,890 --> 00:07:32,620
I can't help the pull of blood.

129
00:07:35,560 --> 00:07:36,560
I'm sorry.

130
00:07:45,870 --> 00:07:47,370
Oh, for crying out loud.

131
00:07:48,710 --> 00:07:52,580
Come on, stop it! Enough!
What is it you want him to say?

132
00:07:53,180 --> 00:07:55,610
He said it's the pull of blood! Blood!

133
00:07:57,420 --> 00:07:58,980
I worried he'd get caught in the rain,

134
00:08:00,280 --> 00:08:02,350
worried he'd be hungry at mealtimes,

135
00:08:02,650 --> 00:08:06,060
I worried he'd catch a cold.
After all that doting...

136
00:08:07,360 --> 00:08:09,030
he says I'm not even his mother!

137
00:08:10,430 --> 00:08:14,800
How can anything be so unfair?

138
00:08:15,870 --> 00:08:17,300
That's not what I meant.

139
00:08:17,370 --> 00:08:20,400
What more do you want from him?
You raised him, and that's enough!

140
00:08:20,870 --> 00:08:22,810
Did you raise him all this time
expecting to be paid back?

141
00:08:24,410 --> 00:08:25,610
Don't try to change the subject.

142
00:08:26,310 --> 00:08:28,050
I'm not even treated like a mother,

143
00:08:29,550 --> 00:08:31,680
but you all get to play happy family.

144
00:08:32,020 --> 00:08:36,290
That's what feels so unfair,
it's driving me crazy! You fool!

145
00:08:44,730 --> 00:08:48,770
It was an absolute whirlwind.
My gosh, my head is still spinning.

146
00:08:49,470 --> 00:08:52,600
CEO Chae has more layers than an onion,
I swear.

147
00:08:52,740 --> 00:08:54,070
Tell me about it.

148
00:08:54,910 --> 00:08:57,940
By the way, did you find out anything
about the Chairman's first wife?

149
00:08:58,080 --> 00:09:02,250
I discreetly asked his office,
but they acted like they knew nothing.

150
00:09:02,480 --> 00:09:06,850
She's the mother of Ma Seo Rin's father.
How can there be no information on her?

151
00:09:07,350 --> 00:09:09,390
This Seong Sil woman,
or whatever her name is,

152
00:09:09,890 --> 00:09:12,020
what if she's not his first wife,
but some new flame, Mom?

153
00:09:12,190 --> 00:09:15,160
Don't be silly!
He's always either at work or at home.

154
00:09:15,230 --> 00:09:17,090
A new mistress?
With me in the picture? Not a chance.

155
00:09:17,460 --> 00:09:18,460
She must be...

156
00:09:19,500 --> 00:09:22,030
Gosh, she must be someone from his past.

157
00:09:24,740 --> 00:09:25,740
Darling.

158
00:09:55,800 --> 00:09:56,800
My.

159
00:09:57,540 --> 00:09:58,540
This is it.

160
00:10:12,850 --> 00:10:15,490
I thought you were in your study,
so I came in,

161
00:10:15,890 --> 00:10:18,790
and I couldn't sleep,
so I was just looking at a book.

162
00:10:19,560 --> 00:10:23,860
Without my permission,
do not come in here as you please.

163
00:10:24,430 --> 00:10:26,230
Yes, I understand.

164
00:10:27,060 --> 00:10:28,070
Gosh.

165
00:10:54,030 --> 00:10:56,460
It definitely looks like my husband
when he was younger.

166
00:10:57,730 --> 00:10:58,900
But something's strange.

167
00:10:59,200 --> 00:11:00,200
What is?

168
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:05,170
Look, this is a baby girl, isn't it?
Look at this headband,

169
00:11:05,570 --> 00:11:09,540
- and this pink outfit she's wearing.
- You're right.

170
00:11:10,440 --> 00:11:14,350
But Oh Jang Mi and Ma Seo Rin's dad,
shouldn't the baby have been a boy?

171
00:11:15,510 --> 00:11:18,880
But this woman...
Her face looks so familiar.

172
00:11:19,820 --> 00:11:22,320
This witch has to be Seong Sil.

173
00:11:22,390 --> 00:11:26,220
Mom, why are you cursing?
What did this woman do to deserve that?

174
00:11:26,290 --> 00:11:30,900
It's because my darling still agonizes
over this photo!

175
00:11:31,530 --> 00:11:34,730
If I ever find her,
I'll scratch her face off.

176
00:11:37,370 --> 00:11:41,640
Jang Mi, you worked so hard today.
You did a great job.

177
00:11:42,540 --> 00:11:44,310
You're such a good girl, Jang Mi.

178
00:11:45,240 --> 00:11:48,010
Mom, your speech seems to have
improved a lot.

179
00:11:48,350 --> 00:11:50,350
You're getting better every day.

180
00:11:50,680 --> 00:11:53,620
Look, Grandma made this for me.

181
00:11:54,220 --> 00:11:56,450
Wow, it's so pretty!

182
00:11:57,120 --> 00:12:01,530
You still have your old touch, Mom.
Like with your cooking.

183
00:12:01,930 --> 00:12:06,330
Yes, Suk Hee makes good side dishes.
Suk Hee makes them delicious.

184
00:12:07,430 --> 00:12:08,430
Right, Mom.

185
00:12:09,030 --> 00:12:12,940
Right. What do we do
about Grandfather's porcelain tea set?

186
00:12:13,140 --> 00:12:16,540
Suk Hee is sorry.
I did it because I was scared.

187
00:12:16,840 --> 00:12:17,840
Mom.

188
00:12:18,380 --> 00:12:22,250
How about we make his favorite food
and bring it to him?

189
00:12:22,410 --> 00:12:23,880
That's a great idea.

190
00:12:24,120 --> 00:12:27,850
Suk Hee will apologize to Grandfather.

191
00:12:28,920 --> 00:12:29,950
Okay, Mom.

192
00:12:40,260 --> 00:12:41,270
Chairman.

193
00:12:49,040 --> 00:12:50,040
Chairman.

194
00:12:50,770 --> 00:12:53,240
- Sir, what is all this?
- Kang Jun Ho.

195
00:12:54,180 --> 00:12:57,110
You're relieved of your duties
as general manager today.

196
00:12:57,750 --> 00:12:58,980
What do you mean, sir?

197
00:12:59,980 --> 00:13:01,990
Is this because of what happened
with the CEO Chae?

198
00:13:03,390 --> 00:13:07,530
- How dare you make a fool of me?
- I didn't know anything.

199
00:13:08,490 --> 00:13:10,130
And neither did CEO Chae.

200
00:13:12,330 --> 00:13:16,400
- We only found out by chance.
- Right. And once you found out,

201
00:13:16,700 --> 00:13:18,570
you got greedy for Dream Group,
didn't you?

202
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:22,410
By manipulating my innocent Seo Rin,

203
00:13:22,540 --> 00:13:25,710
you and your mother are planning
to swallow my company whole.

204
00:13:26,080 --> 00:13:30,380
- Whose brilliant idea was that?
- Chairman...

205
00:13:31,520 --> 00:13:33,850
I have absolutely no interest
in Dream Group.

206
00:13:35,350 --> 00:13:39,190
Lying through your teeth.
You're just like your mother.

207
00:13:39,360 --> 00:13:42,890
If not, why offer to marry my Seo Rin?

208
00:13:42,990 --> 00:13:44,560
Director Ma was the one who wanted it.

209
00:13:45,230 --> 00:13:48,330
- I've never cared for Director Ma.
- What?

210
00:13:48,700 --> 00:13:51,570
A man like you dares to think
about marriage?

211
00:13:52,200 --> 00:13:55,140
A bastard who inherited filthy blood
from who knows where.

212
00:13:55,840 --> 00:13:59,910
You are a liability to Dream Group.
You're fired.

213
00:14:00,310 --> 00:14:01,350
Get out now!

214
00:14:09,650 --> 00:14:10,790
Was that Chairman Ma?

215
00:14:11,790 --> 00:14:14,020
Did that bastard really fire you?

216
00:14:16,530 --> 00:14:19,600
The nerve. How dare he mess with you?

217
00:14:29,470 --> 00:14:32,640
- Jun Ho, what's going on?
- Don't act so surprised.

218
00:14:33,340 --> 00:14:35,180
You have the upper hand now, don't you?

219
00:14:35,580 --> 00:14:39,080
What's that supposed to mean?
Why must you always be so cynical?

220
00:14:39,150 --> 00:14:40,380
I saw this coming.

221
00:14:41,450 --> 00:14:42,890
But don't celebrate just yet.

222
00:14:43,620 --> 00:14:45,060
I'll be back before you know it.

223
00:14:46,020 --> 00:14:47,460
You think it's over for me already?

224
00:14:48,290 --> 00:14:49,290
Not a chance.

225
00:15:01,070 --> 00:15:02,140
Let's go.

226
00:15:07,650 --> 00:15:09,150
Regarding your decision on
General Manager Kang Jun Ho...

227
00:15:09,610 --> 00:15:10,910
Reverse your decision.

228
00:15:11,180 --> 00:15:14,890
- And why should I do that?
- You're asking me why?

229
00:15:16,150 --> 00:15:17,190
In that case...

230
00:15:17,720 --> 00:15:20,120
perhaps I should expose
your entire slush fund.

231
00:15:21,430 --> 00:15:24,900
That Dream Group stock
that you hold so dear.

232
00:15:25,500 --> 00:15:26,930
Want me to turn it into worthless paper?

233
00:15:28,570 --> 00:15:30,270
Don't be ridiculous.

234
00:15:30,330 --> 00:15:34,370
The prosecutors can decide
if I'm being ridiculous or not.

235
00:15:35,510 --> 00:15:37,310
Reinstate me as CEO,

236
00:15:37,710 --> 00:15:40,580
and put my Jun Ho back where he belongs.

237
00:15:41,280 --> 00:15:45,120
If you don't, I'm going straight
to the Prosecutor's Office.

238
00:15:47,750 --> 00:15:49,620
In your dreams.

239
00:15:50,990 --> 00:15:52,260
You think I won't?

240
00:15:53,060 --> 00:15:54,190
A snake like you...

241
00:15:55,060 --> 00:15:58,960
is using your own son
to take over Dream Group.

242
00:16:00,300 --> 00:16:04,400
Don't dream of it.
I built Dream Group with blood and sweat.

243
00:16:04,470 --> 00:16:05,640
It's my company.

244
00:16:06,240 --> 00:16:07,770
The CEO and the heir...

245
00:16:08,570 --> 00:16:09,640
are for me to decide.

246
00:16:10,210 --> 00:16:12,940
- Understand?
- 100 percent of M Company's shares...

247
00:16:13,580 --> 00:16:15,710
have been moved to your shell account,
Chairman.

248
00:16:16,250 --> 00:16:17,680
The documents have been notarized.

249
00:16:18,480 --> 00:16:22,950
A blank power of attorney
CEO Chae signed ten years ago was key.

250
00:16:24,520 --> 00:16:26,690
What? No way.

251
00:16:28,630 --> 00:16:32,500
You shot yourself in the foot
without even realizing it.

252
00:16:40,200 --> 00:16:42,210
No. It can't be.

253
00:16:46,710 --> 00:16:48,780
Manager Lee, M Company...

254
00:16:51,880 --> 00:16:55,350
CEO Chae, we can't withdraw a penny
from M Company.

255
00:16:56,650 --> 00:16:57,720
That's impossible.

256
00:17:00,420 --> 00:17:02,360
Fine, Chairman Ma.

257
00:17:03,160 --> 00:17:05,030
You think I'm going to take this
lying down?

258
00:17:05,600 --> 00:17:06,660
So he's declaring we all go down?

259
00:17:06,930 --> 00:17:09,430
He just declared war
so we all go down together.

260
00:17:10,430 --> 00:17:13,270
That old man has some serious nerve.

261
00:17:23,180 --> 00:17:24,420
Where are you off to, dear?

262
00:17:25,520 --> 00:17:27,520
Isn't Jang Mi home from the office yet?

263
00:17:27,820 --> 00:17:29,020
Seo Rin is here, though.

264
00:17:29,750 --> 00:17:31,360
Are you going somewhere nice?

265
00:17:31,620 --> 00:17:32,660
None of your business.

266
00:17:33,020 --> 00:17:37,430
- Grandfather.
- Jang Mi. Good. Come with me.

267
00:17:38,600 --> 00:17:39,600
Pardon?

268
00:17:43,700 --> 00:17:44,900
You don't know where you're going?

269
00:17:45,570 --> 00:17:48,070
No, he just told me to come along.

270
00:17:48,910 --> 00:17:50,910
- We'll be back.
- Okay.

271
00:17:54,810 --> 00:17:55,850
San Wol.

272
00:17:56,510 --> 00:17:58,050
Did I just see what I think I saw?

273
00:17:58,520 --> 00:18:01,520
Shit. Did Grandfather really leave
with only Oh Jang Mi?

274
00:18:01,920 --> 00:18:02,950
Do you have any idea where they went?

275
00:18:03,020 --> 00:18:06,220
Well, since he couldn't do much
for Jang Mi all this time,

276
00:18:06,660 --> 00:18:08,730
he's probably buying her clothes
or something.

277
00:18:08,790 --> 00:18:11,230
Clothes? As if.
You think Grandfather would do that?

278
00:18:11,930 --> 00:18:13,600
He's probably giving her a building
or some land...

279
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:18,600
Shit. This can't be happening.

280
00:18:19,740 --> 00:18:22,940
Grandfather's introducing Oh Jang Mi
to the board of directors.

281
00:18:22,940 --> 00:18:23,940
What?

282
00:18:23,940 --> 00:18:27,080
He's making her his successor.
Taking my place.

283
00:18:27,140 --> 00:18:30,350
- Oh my, really?
- I'm right, aren't I? Of course I am.

284
00:18:30,880 --> 00:18:33,280
This can't be happening.

285
00:18:33,850 --> 00:18:35,220
Shit!

286
00:18:50,170 --> 00:18:51,640
My love.

287
00:18:52,840 --> 00:18:54,840
I'm here.

288
00:18:56,370 --> 00:19:00,340
Our granddaughter, the one we lost
and have now found again,

289
00:19:01,610 --> 00:19:04,310
I brought her here to meet you,

290
00:19:05,920 --> 00:19:07,520
so please watch over her.

291
00:19:09,790 --> 00:19:10,820
Jang Mi.

292
00:19:11,560 --> 00:19:13,690
Go on, say hello to your grandmother.

293
00:19:15,260 --> 00:19:16,260
Okay.

294
00:19:21,630 --> 00:19:25,840
Grandmother, it's me, Oh Jang Mi.

295
00:19:27,140 --> 00:19:29,070
Though I never got to meet my father,

296
00:19:29,840 --> 00:19:32,240
I feel so safe and reassured
now that Grandfather is with me.

297
00:19:36,380 --> 00:19:38,020
My grandmother's name...

298
00:19:38,550 --> 00:19:42,150
Was it Lee Seong Sil?

299
00:19:42,620 --> 00:19:44,220
Lee Seong Sil.

300
00:19:45,590 --> 00:19:47,520
That was your grandmother's name.

301
00:19:47,990 --> 00:19:51,460
- And my dad's name was...
- You already know. Dong Seok.

302
00:19:52,000 --> 00:19:56,470
So when did she pass away
after having my dad?

303
00:19:59,900 --> 00:20:01,470
Your grandmother...

304
00:20:02,340 --> 00:20:05,480
passed away a long, long time ago.

305
00:20:07,240 --> 00:20:08,580
After losing her daughter,

306
00:20:09,880 --> 00:20:12,180
she grew ill from heartbreak.

307
00:20:13,120 --> 00:20:14,990
She had a daughter?

308
00:20:16,890 --> 00:20:19,720
So that would make her my aunt.

309
00:20:21,930 --> 00:20:24,060
One thing led to another,

310
00:20:25,200 --> 00:20:27,200
I lost them all.

311
00:20:33,200 --> 00:20:34,200
Hwa Young.

312
00:20:34,710 --> 00:20:37,540
I heard Jun Ho was fired
as general manager.

313
00:20:40,040 --> 00:20:41,240
Don't you worry about it.

314
00:20:41,980 --> 00:20:44,480
I'm going to set everything right.

315
00:20:45,150 --> 00:20:47,450
I know you can do it, Hwa Young.

316
00:20:48,090 --> 00:20:51,250
But I'm worried about
the toll it'll take on you.

317
00:20:52,190 --> 00:20:55,190
It must have been awful when Han Young Ja
came barging in, wasn't it?

318
00:20:58,000 --> 00:21:00,260
It's just a hurdle
I knew I'd have to clear.

319
00:21:00,800 --> 00:21:02,700
I'll help you in any way I can.

320
00:21:03,800 --> 00:21:06,470
I'm waiting for the day,

321
00:21:07,070 --> 00:21:08,370
when we can become one family with Jun Ho.

322
00:21:13,480 --> 00:21:14,980
I am too, Nam Bong.

323
00:21:16,110 --> 00:21:17,750
Once all of this is sorted out,

324
00:21:18,150 --> 00:21:21,750
the three of us will build a family
that everyone will envy.

325
00:21:26,690 --> 00:21:28,860
I feel so at ease
whenever I'm with you, Nam Bong.

326
00:21:29,430 --> 00:21:30,930
It's like leaving a battlefield...

327
00:21:31,190 --> 00:21:33,600
and coming back to the safety
of my mother's arms.

328
00:21:36,900 --> 00:21:39,240
I'll be your shield.

329
00:21:39,840 --> 00:21:42,640
I'm always on your side, Hwa Young.

330
00:21:45,340 --> 00:21:47,210
I love you, Hwa Young.

331
00:22:05,160 --> 00:22:07,660
Mom, please eat something,
even if you don't have an appetite.

332
00:22:07,960 --> 00:22:08,970
Okay?

333
00:22:10,700 --> 00:22:11,740
Baek Ho.

334
00:22:12,640 --> 00:22:13,640
You...

335
00:22:14,270 --> 00:22:15,810
You won't leave me, will you?

336
00:22:18,210 --> 00:22:19,510
No matter what happens,

337
00:22:20,610 --> 00:22:23,610
- You'll stay by my side, right?
- Of course I will, Mom.

338
00:22:24,110 --> 00:22:25,380
I'm your son, after all.

339
00:22:28,920 --> 00:22:31,860
Don't be so heartbroken over my brother.

340
00:22:33,590 --> 00:22:35,430
I feel like my whole life
has been for nothing.

341
00:22:35,930 --> 00:22:37,230
What are you talking about?

342
00:22:37,560 --> 00:22:40,030
No one has worked harder
or lived a better life than you.

343
00:22:41,800 --> 00:22:45,000
Jun Ho is just very upset right now,

344
00:22:45,670 --> 00:22:47,270
so he's taking it out on you.

345
00:22:48,000 --> 00:22:49,310
He only does it because you're his mom.

346
00:22:50,510 --> 00:22:51,740
With other people,

347
00:22:52,810 --> 00:22:54,810
you know he never shows
how he's really feeling.

348
00:22:55,450 --> 00:22:56,550
I don't know.

349
00:22:57,850 --> 00:23:00,250
What did I even mean to him?

350
00:23:02,120 --> 00:23:03,290
I just feel so hollow.

351
00:23:05,260 --> 00:23:06,860
All right, this won't do.

352
00:23:07,790 --> 00:23:10,760
That sandwich will be hard to get down.
So I'll go make you some porridge.

353
00:23:17,800 --> 00:23:20,570
- Let's get a divorce.
- What did you say?

354
00:23:20,770 --> 00:23:22,810
- Dad.
- That's ridiculous.

355
00:23:23,270 --> 00:23:26,440
We'll get a divorce when I say so.

356
00:23:26,710 --> 00:23:28,980
What gives you the right
to be the one asking for a divorce?

357
00:23:29,810 --> 00:23:32,580
You're the at-fault party.

358
00:23:33,220 --> 00:23:36,850
You can't divorce me without my consent.
And I will never grant you one.

359
00:23:39,820 --> 00:23:43,690
So you're saying Jun Ho told Lawyer Han
he accepts Chae Hwa Young as his mother?

360
00:23:43,860 --> 00:23:47,730
Yes. My mom's a total wreck right now.

361
00:23:48,330 --> 00:23:52,740
On top of that, my dad is demanding
a divorce to be with CEO Chae.

362
00:23:54,670 --> 00:23:56,810
My family's a complete mess right now.

363
00:23:57,170 --> 00:23:58,480
I feel so awful for Lawyer Han.

364
00:23:59,340 --> 00:24:00,980
She must be so devastated.

365
00:24:02,410 --> 00:24:05,950
Anyway, Baek Ho, I'm worried sick.

366
00:24:06,450 --> 00:24:09,020
Can't we just sue Chae Hwa Young
and make her face legal punishment?

367
00:24:09,320 --> 00:24:12,960
- Grandfather wants that too, right?
- He did at first,

368
00:24:13,690 --> 00:24:16,630
but I think the Chairman is having
second thoughts because of Seo Rin.

369
00:24:17,230 --> 00:24:21,330
And besides, we don't have
enough evidence to proceed right now.

370
00:24:21,400 --> 00:24:25,740
- If we find the wrench, is that proof?
- It would be,

371
00:24:26,040 --> 00:24:29,570
but do you really think Chae Hwa Young
would be so careless with the evidence?

372
00:24:29,740 --> 00:24:32,510
I have to find it, no matter what.
As quickly as possible.

373
00:24:33,680 --> 00:24:35,050
Okay, I'll hang up.

374
00:24:38,950 --> 00:24:39,980
Jun Ho.

375
00:24:48,530 --> 00:24:50,590
I really have to get back inside.

376
00:24:50,930 --> 00:24:52,330
I'm having a really hard day,

377
00:24:53,300 --> 00:24:56,130
and I worked up the courage to come here,
thinking seeing you might help.

378
00:24:56,330 --> 00:24:57,830
Please, don't do this.

379
00:24:58,440 --> 00:25:00,940
I just want the old you back.

380
00:25:01,440 --> 00:25:03,370
If Seo Rin hadn't shown up that day,

381
00:25:05,810 --> 00:25:09,610
- we would be married by now.
- Don't say that. Please just go.

382
00:25:12,680 --> 00:25:14,520
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

383
00:25:23,690 --> 00:25:24,900
Stop it.

384
00:25:26,100 --> 00:25:28,570
Baek Ho is the only one for me.

385
00:25:29,070 --> 00:25:31,800
The more you act like this,
the more I despise you.

386
00:25:32,400 --> 00:25:34,500
- Stop it.
- I don't care.

387
00:25:37,070 --> 00:25:39,340
That's enough for today. I'll be in touch.

388
00:25:40,140 --> 00:25:41,140
Go on inside.

389
00:25:57,690 --> 00:26:00,900
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

390
00:26:09,770 --> 00:26:11,680
Chairman, we need to talk.

391
00:26:15,810 --> 00:26:19,280
This is about the shell company
we've been running together...

392
00:26:19,350 --> 00:26:20,350
Shut up!

393
00:26:20,720 --> 00:26:25,120
This file has M Company transfers
and slush fund details.

394
00:26:25,860 --> 00:26:29,390
I may not have found the money,
but the ledgers still exist.

395
00:26:30,030 --> 00:26:32,260
The proof of everything we've done.

396
00:26:33,230 --> 00:26:34,260
So, what do you say?

397
00:26:35,270 --> 00:26:40,070
How about we both take a nice trip
to prison together?

398
00:26:41,370 --> 00:26:45,410
- How dare you.
- Should I let your Dream Group...

399
00:26:46,010 --> 00:26:47,310
get dragged through scandals
of tax evasion...

400
00:26:47,710 --> 00:26:51,080
and a slush fund?
Is that what you want to see?

401
00:26:53,680 --> 00:26:56,320
I let the fox guard the henhouse.

402
00:26:56,790 --> 00:27:00,420
I never thought you'd stoop this low.

403
00:27:00,590 --> 00:27:03,960
How could you,
after being the head of Dream?

404
00:27:04,130 --> 00:27:06,930
How can you even think of destroying
the company like this?

405
00:27:08,870 --> 00:27:12,900
- Wasn't Dream Group your ultimate goal?
- It still is.

406
00:27:13,570 --> 00:27:16,840
But I have no use for a Dream Group
that doesn't include me.

407
00:27:16,970 --> 00:27:17,970
Is that so?

408
00:27:19,610 --> 00:27:22,710
You must have brought this
because you want to negotiate.

409
00:27:22,810 --> 00:27:24,780
I'm glad you're catching on so quickly.

410
00:27:25,750 --> 00:27:29,690
First, reinstate me as CEO and Jun Ho
as general manager immediately.

411
00:27:30,150 --> 00:27:32,320
And of course,
let me move back into this house.

412
00:27:32,420 --> 00:27:37,060
Also, those indictments accusing me
of child kidnapping,

413
00:27:37,060 --> 00:27:38,500
make them disappear.

414
00:27:46,570 --> 00:27:50,540
How dare you threaten me
with such ridiculous nonsense.

415
00:27:51,410 --> 00:27:54,810
You really thought I'd fall for this?

416
00:27:55,810 --> 00:27:56,810
Fine.

417
00:27:58,050 --> 00:28:01,350
Let's go to prison together.

418
00:28:02,720 --> 00:28:06,290
And we'll see who stays in there longer.

419
00:28:06,720 --> 00:28:08,060
Care to bet?

420
00:28:10,160 --> 00:28:11,160
Father.

421
00:28:39,590 --> 00:28:41,360
(The First Man)

422
00:28:41,520 --> 00:28:45,200
Everyone, this is Chae Hwa Young.
She's joining our team today.

423
00:28:45,500 --> 00:28:47,500
Welcome, Chae Hwa Young.

424
00:28:48,160 --> 00:28:51,230
Apparently, the Chairman approved
Oh Jang Mi and Baek Ho's marriage.

425
00:28:51,600 --> 00:28:54,970
This is no time to be idle.
Are you just going to do nothing?

426
00:28:55,570 --> 00:28:57,570
The Chairman has a daughter?

427
00:28:57,710 --> 00:29:01,510
What are you talking about?
A daughter besides Dong Seok?

428
00:29:03,850 --> 00:29:05,850
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
